phones.description: When set to true, will only return a match if phones are present

emails.description: When set to true, will only return a match if emails are present

post.description: Skiptrace up to 1,000 people in one API call

parameters.name: x-user-id
parameters.description: Denote a unique user identifier to this api call by passing it in this header field

skips.description: An array of contacts that you will would like to have skipped and returned with demographic profiles, including phone numbers and emails

key.description: An internal key provided by you that will help you connect requests going into the API to the responses that hit your webhook

webhook_url.description: The location where you would like to receive the responses for each of the individual requests sent to this endpoint

phone.description: Phone must be 10 digits without any formatting & cannot contain any alpha characters or special characters

address.description: If you provide address, city, state, and zip then the mailing address parts aren't required but they can still be provided

mail_address.description: If you provide mail_address, mail_city, mail_state, and mail_zip then the regular address parts aren't required but they can still be provided

webcomplete_url.description: must be a valid https POST endpoint.  The webhook_url should return a https status of 200.  The response body can be empty.

code-samples.code:
curl --request POST \
  --url https://api.realestateapi.com/v1/SkipTraceBatch \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --header 'x-api-key: <your-api-key>' \
  --data '{
  "match_requirements": {
  	"phones": true,
    "emails": true,
    "social": true
  },
  "webcomplete_url": "https://myServer.com/api/myWebhookEndpt",
  "skips": [
    {
	    "key": 1,
      "webhook_url": "<Your Webhook Url>",
      "first_name": "Jane",
      "last_name": "Smith",
      "address": "123 Main St",
      "city": "Herndon",
      "state": "VA",
      "zip": "20170"
    },
    {
      "key": 2,
      "webhook_url": "<Your Webhook Url>",
      "first_name": "Joe",
      "last_name": "Nelson",
      "address": "1000 New St",
      "city": "Reston",
      "state": "VA",
      "zip": "20194",
      "mail_address": "2000 Another St",
      "mail_city": "Reston",
      "mail_state": "VA",
      "mail_zip": "20194"
    }
  ]
}'
code-samples.name: Bulk Skip Request Sample

post.description: Need to call the Bulk SkipTrace API and don't want to sweat the Webhook setup or need to return results directly to the calling thread? Use this endpoint to get the identity and demographic data you need and call it via 'await' keywords in programming languages that support such syntax.

webhook_url.description: The location where you would like to receive the responses for each of the individual requests sent to this endpoint

phone.description: Phone must be 10 digits without any formatting & cannot contain any alpha characters or special characters

address.description: If you provide address, city, state, and zip then the mailing address parts aren't required but they can still be provided
